sentences: Ari Pulkkinen (born 15 January 1982) is a Finnish video game composer, musician and sound designer.
He won many music competitions and made his first big public album to accompany a freeware game named "Starfight VI: Gatekeepers" in 1999.
In 2003 he was hired as in-house audio director to game development company Frozenbyte Inc.
After quitting Frozenbyte in 2008 (though he continues to have a professional relationship with them), Ari started his own sound production company AriTunes.
On 2 September 2011 in Video Game Heroes Concert, Angry Birds Theme was played by London Philharmonic Orchestra.
On 4 October 2011, Ari won the Best Finnish Game Developer in 2011 Award due to his contribution in the Finnish game industry.
